OL,3,CSpecsavers co-founder dedicates royal
OL,4,Chonour to his staff
OL,6,FThe co-founder of Specsavers has
OL,7,Fdedicated his CBE for services to
OL,8,Fbusiness and trade to his staff.
OL,10,FDoug Perkins was formally presented
OL,11,Fwith the Commander of the British
OL,12,FEmpire title by the Princess Royal at
OL,13,FWindsor Castle.
OL,15,FHe was joined by his family, including
OL,16,Fhis wife, Dame Mary Perkins; together
OL,17,Fthey created Specsavers in Guernsey in
OL,18,F1984, growing the family business from
OL,19,Fa small opticians to the largest
OL,20,Fprivate eye and hearing care provider
OL,21,Fin the world.
