OL,3,CSpecsavers co-founder dedicates royal
OL,4,Chonour to his staff
OL,6,FDuring his studies, he met Mary and
OL,7,Fthey founded their first business -
OL,8,FBebbington and Perkins Opticians -
OL,9,Fwhich they sold in 1980 before moving
OL,10,Fto Guernsey to be closer to Mary's
OL,11,Fparents.
OL,13,FDespite Specsavers' size, it has
OL,14,Fremained family-owned, with their son
OL,15,FJohn now CEO and four of their seven
OL,16,Fgrandchildren also involved in the
OL,17,Fbusiness.
OL,19,FAlso honoured at the ceremony was the
OL,20,FGreggs CEO Roisin Currie and BBC
OL,21,Fjournalist Martha Kearney.
